&lt;p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'>&lt;span
style='font-size:14.0pt'>“Where Is God?”&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal>&lt;span style='font-size:14.0pt'>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span>&lt;/p>
&lt;p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify;text-indent:.5in'>Not only is God
someone we &lt;u>don’t&lt;/u> see; he is someone we &lt;u>can’t&lt;/u> see (1 Timothy &lt;b>3&lt;/b>:16).
We may wonder, though, why he doesn’t show himself someway at least once in a
while. He could speak to us audibly or give us a vision of himself from time to
time. The short answer to the question is, “We don’t know.”&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>JUST A THOUGHT 'Where Is God?'</title><link>https://christir.org/essays/topics/just-a-thought/just-a-thought-where-is-god/</link><pubDate>Thu, 02 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://christir.org/essays/topics/just-a-thought/just-a-thought-where-is-god/</guid><description>&lt;style>
